In article <199407071833.NAA11644@indial1.io.com>, ritter@io.com (Terry
Ritter) writes:

>One way to minimize the possibility of an
>effective future attack is to use a much stronger primitive.

Agreed, that is _one_ way.  It is the cryptographer's way.  As a security
person, I use the information provided to me by the cryptographer about
what he knows about the strength and limits of his product.  I never rely
exclusively upon what cryptographers tell me.
